It is not an url, it is relative path, which should always be "TelemetryService/{SomeID}", so I thought that object_path semantics would be good here. But it turned out, that sdbusplus object_path should not work with relative paths, according to the comment in: https://github.com/openbmc/sdbusplus/blob/master/src/message/native_types.cpp

  std::string string_path_wrapper::filename() const
  {
    ...
    // Dbus paths must start with /, if we don't find one, it's an error
    ...
  }

Currently sdbusplus code doesn't really check if path starts with '/', so my solution works just fine, but now I see that I should not take it for granted.

So in summary, we have relative path-like string. It is not an url and not an object_path. What do you suggest to parse it properly?
